<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="486" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d486">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Defense Files: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of State to the Acting Secretary of
                                    State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">
                                    <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1">Argonaut</gloss>
                                </hi> 71A. Crypto-War for Acting Secretary of State only from
                                Secretary <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">Stettinius</persName>.</p>
                            <p>The British are disturbed over our having entered into an aviation
                                agreement with Ireland<note n="1" xml:id="d486fn1">For the text of
                                    this agreement relating to air-transport service, which was
                                    signed at Washington February 3, 1945, see Department of State
                                    Executive Agreement Series No. 460, or 59 <gloss target="#t_Stat1">Stat</gloss>. 1402.</note> without
                                consulting or informing them. Please send us promptly an appropriate
                                explanation for us to present to the British on this matter.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">
                                        <gloss target="#t_ARGONAUT1"><placeName>Argonaut</placeName></gloss></hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-07">February 7,
                                        1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>